summary: This code imports the Telnet library, establishes a connection to localhost on port 10000, sends "hello world\n" over the connection, reads until a newline character is received, and then prints the response.

details.comment: This code imports the Telnet library, establishes a connection to localhost on port 10000, sends "hello world\n" over the connection, reads until a newline character is received, and then prints the response.
details.content:
from telnetlib import Telnet
t = Telnet("localhost",10000)
t.write(b"hello world\n")
c=t.read_until(b"\n")
print(c)
